# Test Custom Database Connections

If you use the Auth0-hosted database structure to store your users, you can test the connection by authenticating users against the same or a separate tenant.

## Test with import users to Auth0 enabled

When import users is enabled, users are gradually migrated from your external user store to Auth0 user store. In the process, users will be authenticated against the external store the first time they successfully log in. All further login attempts will be executed against the Auth0 user store. To learn more, read about automatic migrations in [Import and Export Users](https://auth0.com/docs/manage-users/user-migration).

### Create a test tenant and application

